The paper deals with the problem of super-resolution, which is a common topic in signal processing and image analysis. The use of low-pass Fourier measurements and convex optimization methods suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Signal Processing (cs.SP) categories. Additionally, the paper specifically mentions the use of Phase Space transformations, which are commonly used in computer vision and image processing, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Multimedia (cs.MM) categories. Finally, the use of Total Variation minimization suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) category.
